{
  "texts": [
    "This suggests that our RL recipe is effective not only for long-form deep research tasks, but also generalizes well to short-form QA.",
    "Including both long-form and short-form SFT data is helpful.",
    "Figure 6 reports an ablation of the SFT training mixture.",
    "We analyze (i) removing the long-form or short-form subsets entirely, and (ii) subsampling the full corpus uniformly at random.",
    "Many existing open deep research models are trained only on short-form QA, assuming that short-form supervision will transfer to long-form synthesis, while other systems are optimized purely for long-form reporting and struggle to produce concise answers."
  ]
}